T1  - On the optimal choice of capital intensity in LDCs with migration
AU  - Stark, Oded
JO  - Journal of Development Economics
VL  - 9
IS  - 1
SP  - 31
EP  - 41
PY  - 1981
DA  - 1981/08/01/
SN  - 0304-3878
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(81)90003-1
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387881900031
AB  - Sen's classic work on the choice of capital intensity of investment is generalized in the light of new theoretical developments and empirical findings concerning rural-to-urban migration in LDCs. This is done by explicitly incorporating a migration function into the basic choice model. Revised conditions for maximization of surplus are derived and compared with Sen's original condition. Some justification for the particular migration function used in the presence of risk- aversion is suggested.
